    "about_intro": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "intro_eyebrow": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Our Story",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "intro_text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Shoeless Joe's Cards is proudly operated by brothers Kevin and Dan Burke, lifelong Cincinnati residents and passionate collectors. We've been visiting Shoeless Joe's since it first opened its doors and have deep roots in the local hobby community.</p><p>In 2022, during the hobby's post-COVID resurgence, we launched our own card business focused on grading, collecting, and resale. Our experience includes 1,000+ card submissions to PSA, BGS, SGC, and other grading companies. We've been active on eBay since 2001 and continue to engage with PWCC, Goldin, Collectors, Fanatics, and Rally Rd.</p><p>Our goal is to blend the classic card-shop feel of Shoeless Joe's with modern tools and services that meet the needs of today's collectors.</p>",
            "text_size": "t2"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["intro_eyebrow", "intro_text"],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "center",
        "content_max_width": "m",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "center",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "section_color_scheme": "scheme-1203590d-2999-412a-986f-d063dd6d00f1",
        "top_padding": "pt-s15",
        "bottom_padding": "pb-s"
      }
    },

    "era_1": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "h1b": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "The Beginning — Mid-1990s",
            "heading_size": "h2",
            "heading_tag": "h2"
          }
        },
        "t1b": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Cards, Creamy Whip &amp; Community.</strong> Before it became a Cincinnati hobby staple, Shoeless Joe's started as a baseball card shop and neighborhood creamy whip — serving slushies, nachos, and summertime memories. The early signage is something many locals still remember.</p>",
            "text_size": "t2"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": ["h1b", "t1b"],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_section_height": 460,
        "mobile_section_height": 380,
